Pre-Game Insights: The Subway Socceroos take on India to begin its AFC Asian Cup Qatar 2023™ on Saturday at 10:30pm AEDT.
This will be the ninth meeting against India and first since the 2011 iteration of the Asian Cup where the Aussies recorded a 4-0 triumph in the opening match.
Australia has been pitted in Group B alongside India, Syria, and Uzbekistan with all of its Group B matches kicking off at 10:30pm AEDT.
Graham Arnold announced his 26-man squad for the tournament, determined to build on its recent strong form over the last 12 months.
Miscellaneous Highlights: All matches involving Australia at the AFC Asian Cup Qatar 2023™ will be broadcast Live and Free on Australia's 'Home of Football,' Network 10 as well as streamed live via both 10 Play and Paramount+.
Every AFC Asian Cup Qatar 2023 Match will be Live on Paramount+.
International fans can check the official global broadcasters in each territory here.
Australia v India will take place on Saturday, 13 January 2024 at Ahmad bin Ali Stadium, Al Rayyan with a kick-off at 2:30pm local (10:30pm AEDT).
